title: Grateful Dead Live at Meadowlands Arena on 1983-04-16
lineage: SBD > MC > DAT > CDR > EAC > shntool > mkwACT > SHN
description: Minglewood Blues, Tennessee Jed, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Bird Song, My Brother Esau, West L.A. Fadeaway, Maybe You Know, Looks Like Rain-> Touch Of Gray China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Uncle John's Band-> Truckin'-> Drumz-> Black Queen*-> Iko Iko*-> Bob Star-> The Other One-> Black Peter-> One More Saturday Night*, E: Johnny B. Goode*

reviews.review_text:
Stepen Stills Stephen Stills was playing near by & stopped in both nights!!! Was awesome!!! 1st Black Queen since 12-10-69 & last one. Here is the link to get the 1st time played & it was with Stephen Stills!!! http://www.archive.org/audio/etree-details-db.php?id=12934 enjoy!!

S. Hanley
Waikiki, Hi.
HSSSSSSSSS The hiss on this recording sounds like a whole new instrument. Jerry's guitar work on Looks Like Rain is classic. Great fun at both of these shows. What a great year

peak year me and my companion Jake enjoyed this Brendan byrne show and to our surprise Stephen Stills showed up as surprise special guest.Black queen and iko iko blew us away. i recieved this concert on cassette the following week.the sound quality with this show only got better.

What a show! Still remember this 2nd set like it was yesterday! The first 4 tunes-China Cat>Rider>Uncle John>Truckin' is as close to a Dead greatest hits package as one can get....and then joined by Stills for a steamin' set of tunes....

Thanks for taping and posting!

Jeff Z.
Brooklyn, NY

Rippin show!!! This was a great night...had alot of fun, steve stills.. black queen, iko was a groovin time.. the other one was incredible too. the whole nite rocked lots of speculation in the air would stills show up tomoro night?? he did !! love the one your with.....such a great time  seems like just yesterday...peace :)

cool show really liked the first set, and find the 'bobstar' thing interesting -- 'just wanna hang up there and be a little star' -- very spaced. like it. enjoyable show, but highlight of evening was the band's 'hospitality suite' back at parker meridian on 56th street. no comment on the proceedings :-)
